claim: There are no Los Angeles K-12 schools with more than 500 free meals and fewer than 700 free or reduced-price meals.
reasoning: The database contains many Los Angeles K-12 schools with Free Meal Count (K-12) > 500 and FRPM Count (K-12) < 700. For example, Slauson Intermediate has 523 free meals and 648 FRPM, Felicitas and Gonzalo Mendez High has 675 free meals and 685 FRPM, and over 200 other schools meet these criteria. The claim that no such schools exist is directly contradicted by the data.
